en_153499_0	A group of disabled war heroes from the police and STF have launched a protest in front of Colombo Fort Railway Station demanding pensions and promotions.
en_153499_1	Chairman of Sri Lanka Police disabled war heroes association Asela Kumara told our news team that the department has delayed granting them pensions and promotions.
en_153499_2	However, the government stated on an earlier occasion that the pension for disabled war heroes who served for less than 10 years and other ranking officers who have not completed 12 years in service would be paid out pensions effective from this month.
